gner function representation is identical\n\nwith the classical expression. The standard \u02c6x representation can be calculated either directly or via inverse Fourier\n\ntransform of the Wigner function:\n\n\u03c1(x\u2032, x\u2032\u2032) =\n\n\u0012 1\n\nL\n\n\u0013\n\ne\u2212m\n\n2\u03b2 [x\u2032\u2212x\u2032\u2032]2\n\n(52.50)\n\nOptionally it can be regarded as a special case of the harmonic oscillator case.", "embedding": [-0.019904843, -0.027784737, 0.03230845, -0.0025882877, -0.010957412, -0.038319953, -0.022174206, -0.02621484, -0.07772179, 0.08698819, 0.061535537, 0.008890907, 0.011058124, -0.0076403082, -0.026774451, 0.017793234, -0.018968798, -0.03958805, -0.06966525, -0.00059768755, 0.03328153, 0.008151991, -0.076150894, -0.028553095, -0.03614095, 0.011837617, 0.018835273, 0.010680313, 0.045771383, 0.032972503, 0.0418851, -0.029433727, 0.0017055888, -0.03707576, 0.0067920485, -0.001391484, 0.026665574, -0.0156119475, 0.026911123, -0.007894491, 0.06684015, 0.010724124, 0.012405061, -0.013389025, -0.009826319, -0.027434658, -0.006324331, 0.035188206, -0.017954357, -0.05487327, 0.012162666, -0.003325378, 0.050318964, -0.052357163, -0.020784197, -0.01164751, -0.0046647545, 0.02764693, -0.0011339439, 0.0172582, 0.0257159, 0.0018686028, 0.0037285767, -0.029412193, 0.006406545, 0.041815456, -0.04525931, 0.077317506, 0.0089766355, -0.046276424, 0.021804359, -0.018703688, -0.037023198, 0.033744246, -0.028018849, 0.053866483, -0.017146697, -0.034195945, -0.04447872, 0.0033031625, -0.0037603702, -0.014189759, -0.0067794356, 0.024186756, 0.0065665804, -0.010952322, -0.014254896, -0.0017276326, 0.0109474575, -0.00021210106, 0.010392258, 0.06455564, 0.00097155373, -0.027038544, 0.020381572, 0.012021503, 0.022278884, 0.034768697, 0.029258968, 0.029666798, -0.0012223844, 0.081520334, -0.009028854, 0.049559824, 0.0147036975, 0.058796365, -0.0055883974, 0.017970724, -0.027915694, -0.04440603, 0.009841476, -0.032614667, -0.016348515, 0.0007552068, 0.012994604, 0.02033192,